			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Was in a GoD raid trial the other day and the raid had 6-7 adds.  All the adds casted some kind of AoE or tash on the group, but the chanters in the raid proceeded to mez them.  What happened next is I got 6 unable to break mesmerized target message, then the pet decides to cast bull rush and breaks the mes on a target.
<br />

<br />
Never had this happen before until I started using /pet focus.  If you had something similar happen please /bug it and ask for our AA points back, this "bug" was not in the description, and until it's fixed we should get our points back.
<br />

<br />
And also on second thought, I realised the purpose of this advanced pet discipline 2 AA of /pet no spell, it is to fix the advanced pet discpline 1 !! so the focused pet wont break mes !!  So... we spend 5 AA to get a broken ability... and another 3 to decrease our pet dps and fix it ?
<br />

<br />
Maybe the pet's abilities like water elemental strike and bull rush should be changed to a proc (like beastlord pets) instead of a special ability.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
